<p style="font-size: 70px; margin-bottom: -10px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.5">&ldquo;</p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 30px;">The thing I love about this lesson is how visual it is. It gives students a shared experience that we can all refer back to later. Students have the chance to be the computer. They get to walk through each of the steps on a simplified level. By the end, they actually understand what A.I. Bot is doing when it is making a decision. 

This lesson also gave my students the opportunity to see that there is an element of opinion in classification systems. When deciding how sweet something is, there is not a right or wrong answer. It's an opinion. Later, when we started to see how bias can end up in AI, I was able to pull them back and remind them that the data used to train their models was based on choices. I am not sure that this light bulb moment happened during Lesson 5, but the lesson laid the foundation for the light bulb moment to happen later.
</p>
