## Role of the teacher

##### Teachers are the key component that make lesson plans come alive for students. Teachers know their students best and are best positioned to make choices to increase engagement within a lesson. This might mean adding a visual or tactile aspect to an existing activity, incorporating movement, shifting a whole group discussion to a small group discussion, etc. Planning for engagement is an essential piece of planning for a Code.org lesson. 

